Let $ABCD$ be an isoceles trapezoid having parallel bases $\overline{AB}$ and $\overline{CD}$ with $AB>CD.$ Line segments from a point inside $ABCD$ to the vertices divide the trapezoid into four triangles whose areas are $2, 3, 4,$ and $5$ starting with the triangle with base $\overline{CD}$ and moving clockwise as shown in the diagram below. What is the ratio $\frac{AB}{CD}?$
\begin{center}

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
unitsize(100);
pair A=(-1, 0), B=(1, 0), C=(0.3, 0.9), D=(-0.3, 0.9), P=(0.2, 0.5), E=(0.1, 0.75), F=(0.4, 0.5), G=(0.15, 0.2), H=(-0.3, 0.5); 
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle, black); 
draw(A--P, black);
draw(B--P, black);
draw(C--P, black);
draw(D--P, black);
label("$A$",A,(-1,0));
label("$B$",B,(1,0));
label("$C$",C,(1,-0));
label("$D$",D,(-1,0));
label("$2$",E,(0,0));
label("$3$",F,(0,0));
label("$4$",G,(0,0));
label("$5$",H,(0,0));
dot(A^^B^^C^^D^^P);

\end{asy}
\\

\end{center}

$\textbf{(A)}\: 3\qquad\textbf{(B)}\: 2+\sqrt{2}\qquad\textbf{(C)}\: 1+\sqrt{6}\qquad\textbf{(D)}\: 2\sqrt{3}\qquad\textbf{(E)}\: 3\sqrt{2}$
